## Technical Architecture Considerations

### Multi-Tenancy

- Each church has isolated data (database per tenant or schema separation)
- Subdomain or church ID routing
- Shared infrastructure with tenant-specific customization
- Scalable architecture to handle growth

### Real-Time Features

- WebSocket connections for chat
- Push notifications for prayer requests, assignments
- Live updates for service changes
- Real-time attendance tracking

### Offline Support

- Core features work offline
- Sync when connection restored
- Offline message queuing
- Cached data for key features

### Security & Privacy

- End-to-end encryption for sensitive data
- GDPR and data privacy compliance
- Audit logs for sensitive actions
- Two-factor authentication option
- Data export for members (GDPR right to data portability)

### Scalability

- Designed to handle 100+ churches
- Support churches from 50 to 5000+ members
- Efficient data queries with proper indexing
- CDN for media assets
- Background job processing for heavy tasks

